    "what_description": "Lathyrus hispanicus is a perennial flowering plant belonging to the family Fabaceae, native to the Iberian Peninsula. It has a height of 30-60 cm, with a taproot and a slender stem bearing alternate, compound leaves with 5-7 pairs of leaflets, and a terminal raceme of 5-10 pink or purple flowers. The flowers are 1.5-2 cm long, with a calyx of 5 fused sepals, and a corolla of 5 fused petals. The plant produces a pod 5-7 cm long, containing 2-4 seeds. Lathyrus hispanicus prefers well-drained soil and full sun to partial shade, and is typically found in grasslands and rocky outcrops.",
